.TH QD2CSV 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-qdtools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
qd2csv \- print point querydata as CSV
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qd2csv
.RB [ \-latlon ]
.I querydata
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qd2csv
reads point (station) querydata and prints all observations as
comma-separated values on standard output. Times are printed in UTC.
.PP
The output contains one row per (station, time) pair, with one column
per non-empty parameter. Columns containing only missing values are
omitted. Missing values within retained columns are written as
.BR NA .
.PP
Column names are built from the parameter name and, for non-surface
data, a level suffix:
.RS 4
_P\fIvalue\fR for pressure levels,
.br
_M\fIvalue\fR for mean-sea-level data,
.br
_A\fIvalue\fR for altitude,
.br
_H\fIvalue\fR for height,
.br
_L\fIvalue\fR for hybrid (model) levels.
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-latlon
Include station latitude and longitude as the second and third columns
of every row.
.SH EXAMPLES
Convert a station file to CSV:
.PP
.RS 4
qd2csv stations.sqd > stations.csv
.RE
.PP
Include coordinates:
.PP
.RS 4
qd2csv \-latlon stations.sqd > stations.csv
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR csv2qd (1),
.BR qdpoint (1),
.BR qdinfo (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-qdtools/issues>.
